---
/**
 * SPRAVATO billing guide - targeting clinics offering esketamine
 */
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

const allSoftware = await getCollection('software');
const spravatoCabable = allSoftware.filter(
  (s) => s.data.ketamine_features.spravato_workflows ||
    s.data.description.toLowerCase().includes('spravato') ||
    s.data.general_features?.some(f => f.feature.toLowerCase().includes('spravato'))
);

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: 'SPRAVATO Billing Guide for Mental Health Practices',
  description: 'Complete guide to SPRAVATO billing codes, REMS compliance, and reimbursement for psychiatry practices offering esketamine treatment.',
  author: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'Ketamine Software Directory',
  },
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SPRAVATO Billing Guide 2026 - Codes, REMS Compliance & Reimbursement"
  description="Complete guide to SPRAVATO (esketamine) billing for psychiatry practices. CPT codes, HCPCS codes, REMS compliance, insurance authorization, and EHR requirements."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <!-- Breadcrumb -->
  <nav class="border-b border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 px-4 py-3 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <ol class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
        <li>
          <a href="/" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-700">Home</a>
        </li>
        <li class="text-slate-400">/</li>
        <li>
          <a href="/guides/" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-700">Guides</a>
        </li>
        <li class="text-slate-400">/</li>
        <li class="text-slate-900">SPRAVATO Billing Guide</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- Article -->
  <article class="px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <!-- Header -->
      <header>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
          SPRAVATO Billing Guide
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-600">
          A practical guide to billing, coding, and REMS compliance for practices offering SPRAVATO (esketamine) treatment.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-slate-500">
          <span>10 min read</span>
          <span>Â·</span>
          <span>Last updated: January 2026</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <!-- Important Notice -->
      <div class="mt-10 rounded-xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-6">
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <svg class="h-6 w-6 shrink-0 text-amber-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m9-.75a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0zm-9 3.75h.008v.008H12v-.008z" />
          </svg>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-800">Disclaimer</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-amber-700">
              This guide is for informational purposes only and is not billing or legal advice. Always verify current codes and requirements with your payers and compliance team. Billing rules change frequently.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Table of Contents -->
      <nav class="mt-10 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-6">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li><a href="#overview" class="text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700">1. SPRAVATO Overview</a></li>
          <li><a href="#rems" class="text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700">2. REMS Certification Requirements</a></li>
          <li><a href="#billing-codes" class="text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700">3. Billing Codes (CPT & HCPCS)</a></li>
          <li><a href="#authorization" class="text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700">4. Prior Authorization</a></li>
          <li><a href="#documentation" class="text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700">5. Documentation Requirements</a></li>
          <li><a href="#software" class="text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700">6. Software with SPRAVATO Support</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-gray mt-12 max-w-none">
        <h2 id="overview">SPRAVATO Overview</h2>
        <p>
          SPRAVATO (esketamine nasal spray) is FDA-approved for treatment-resistant depression (TRD) and major depressive disorder (MDD) with suicidal ideation. Unlike IV ketamine, SPRAVATO is covered by many insurance plans, but billing requires navigating a complex REMS program and specific coding requirements.
        </p>

        <h3>Key Differences from IV Ketamine</h3>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Aspect</th>
              <th>SPRAVATO</th>
              <th>IV Ketamine</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>FDA Approval</td>
              <td>Yes (TRD, MDD with SI)</td>
              <td>Off-label for depression</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Insurance Coverage</td>
              <td>Often covered</td>
              <td>Usually cash-pay</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Administration</td>
              <td>Nasal spray, self-administered</td>
              <td>IV infusion by provider</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Monitoring</td>
              <td>2+ hours post-administration</td>
              <td>During infusion</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>REMS</td>
              <td>Required</td>
              <td>Not applicable</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2 id="rems">REMS Certification Requirements</h2>
        <p>
          SPRAVATO requires enrollment in the REMS (Risk Evaluation and Mitigation Strategy) program before you can prescribe or administer.
        </p>

        <h3>Healthcare Setting Requirements</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Complete REMS enrollment via the SPRAVATO portal</li>
          <li>Staff must be certified (prescribers and healthcare staff who monitor)</li>
          <li>Patient must be enrolled and complete Patient Enrollment Form</li>
          <li>Document compliance with monitoring requirements</li>
          <li>Drug cannot leave the healthcare setting</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Per-Visit REMS Compliance</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Verify patient hasn't eaten for 2 hours, drunk liquids for 30 minutes</li>
          <li>Confirm patient has arranged transportation (cannot drive day of treatment)</li>
          <li>Monitor blood pressure before dosing</li>
          <li>Patient self-administers under supervision</li>
          <li>Monitor for 2+ hours post-administration</li>
          <li>Document all REMS requirements were met</li>
          <li>Complete the PDSS (Patient Status Sheet) form</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="billing-codes">Billing Codes</h2>

        <h3>Drug Codes (HCPCS)</h3>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Code</th>
              <th>Description</th>
              <th>Dose</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>J3305</code></td>
              <td>SPRAVATO (esketamine) nasal spray</td>
              <td>1 mg</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>
          <strong>Important:</strong> J3305 is billed per 1mg. A 56mg dose = 56 units. An 84mg dose = 84 units.
        </p>

        <h3>Administration & Observation Codes (CPT)</h3>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Code</th>
              <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>90899</code></td>
              <td>Unlisted psychiatric service (sometimes used)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>99211-99215</code></td>
              <td>E/M office visit (for assessment)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>96372</code></td>
              <td>Therapeutic injection (not always applicable)</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Place of Service</h3>
        <p>
          Use <strong>POS 11</strong> (Office) for outpatient administration. SPRAVATO must be administered in a certified healthcare setting.
        </p>

        <h3>Common Modifier Usage</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>JW</strong> - Drug amount discarded (if applicable)</li>
          <li>Check payer-specific modifier requirements</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="authorization">Prior Authorization</h2>
        <p>
          Most payers require prior authorization for SPRAVATO. Common requirements include:
        </p>

        <h3>Medical Necessity Documentation</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Diagnosis of TRD (failed 2+ antidepressants) or MDD with suicidal ideation</li>
          <li>Documentation of previous treatments and failures</li>
          <li>Current PHQ-9 or MADRS scores</li>
          <li>Treatment plan with frequency and duration</li>
          <li>REMS enrollment confirmation</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Common Payer Requirements</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>United Healthcare:</strong> Step therapy documentation, PA required</li>
          <li><strong>Aetna:</strong> Must meet TRD criteria, PA required</li>
          <li><strong>BCBS:</strong> Varies by state, typically PA required</li>
          <li><strong>Medicare:</strong> Covered under Part D, check specific plan</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="documentation">Documentation Requirements</h2>
        <p>
          Proper documentation is essential for billing compliance and REMS adherence:
        </p>

        <h3>Each Treatment Session Must Document</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Pre-treatment blood pressure</li>
          <li>Dose administered (56mg or 84mg)</li>
          <li>Time of administration</li>
          <li>Monitoring observations (typically every 30 min)</li>
          <li>Post-treatment blood pressure (before discharge)</li>
          <li>Dissociative symptoms if any</li>
          <li>Patient discharged with transportation (documented)</li>
          <li>PDSS form completed</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>EHR Template Recommendations</h3>
        <p>
          Your EHR should have templates that capture:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>REMS compliance checklist (built into workflow)</li>
          <li>Vital signs table with timestamps</li>
          <li>Dissociation scale documentation</li>
          <li>Patient status at discharge</li>
          <li>Next appointment scheduling</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="software">Software with SPRAVATO Support</h2>
        <p>
          The following EHR systems have documented SPRAVATO billing or workflow support:
        </p>

        {spravatoCabable.length > 0 ? (
          <ul>
            {spravatoCabable.map((s) => (
              <li>
                <a href={`/software/${s.data.slug}/`} class="text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700">
                  {s.data.name}
                </a>
                {' '}- {s.data.description.substring(0, 100)}...
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        ) : (
          <p>
            Currently, <a href="/software/advancedmd/" class="text-teal-600">AdvancedMD</a> is known for strong SPRAVATO REMS billing support. Many practices also use general behavioral health EHRs with custom templates.
          </p>
        )}

        <h3>Key EHR Features for SPRAVATO</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>REMS compliance tracking built into workflow</li>
          <li>Vital signs documentation with timestamps</li>
          <li>Prior authorization tracking</li>
          <li>Buy-and-bill inventory management</li>
          <li>J-code billing support</li>
          <li>Automated PDSS form generation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="mt-12 rounded-xl border border-teal-200 bg-teal-50 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Need SPRAVATO-Ready Software?</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
          Compare EHR options with SPRAVATO billing support and REMS compliance features.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/software/"
          class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center rounded-lg bg-teal-600 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-teal-700"
        >
          Browse Software
          <svg class="ml-2 h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5 21 12m0 0-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
